/* angled collage-style accents behind headings */
.accent-chip{
  position:absolute;inset:auto auto 0 0;width:120px;height:70px;
  transform:rotate(-6deg);background:var(--accent-2);opacity:.85;
}
.accent-chip.alt{background:var(--accent-1);transform:rotate(9deg);}

/* minimal control styling */
.ui input[type="range"]{width:100%;}
.ui button{
  background:var(--accent-1);border:none;color:var(--ink);
  padding:6px 10px;border-radius:4px;cursor:pointer;
}
.ui button:focus{outline:2px solid var(--ink);outline-offset:2px;}
.ui input:focus{outline:2px solid var(--accent-1);}

3D viewport styling
	•	Renderer clear color must be black.
	•	Add a starfield. Do not place warm surface colors behind the canvas.

Create src/scene/starfield.ts:

import * as THREE from "three";

export function makeStarfield(count=4000, radius=1200){
  const geo=new THREE.BufferGeometry();
  const pos=new Float32Array(count*3);
  for(let i=0;i<count;i++){
    const r=radius*(0.6+Math.random()*0.4);
    const th=Math.random()*Math.PI*2;
    const ph=Math.acos(2*Math.random()-1);
    pos[i*3+0]=r*Math.sin(ph)*Math.cos(th);
    pos[i*3+1]=r*Math.sin(ph)*Math.sin(th);
    pos[i*3+2]=r*Math.cos(ph);
  }
  geo.setAttribute("position",new THREE.BufferAttribute(pos,3));
  const mat=new THREE.PointsMaterial({size:1.2,sizeAttenuation:true,color:0xffffff});
  const pts=new THREE.Points(geo,mat);
  pts.frustumCulled=false;
  return pts;
}

In scene init:

renderer.setClearColor(0x000000,1);
scene.add(makeStarfield());

Labels inside the 3D scene

Use Three.js CSS2DRenderer for crisp HTML labels that track points.

.label{
  font-family:var(--font-serif);font-weight:700;font-size:14px;
  color:var(--ink);
  background:color-mix(in oklab,var(--cream) 85%, white 15%);
  padding:4px 8px;border-radius:4px;
  border:1px solid color-mix(in oklab,var(--ink) 12%, transparent);
  box-shadow:0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,.18);
}
.label--accent{color:var(--maroon);}

Apply .label to “North Node” and “South Node”. Use .label--accent for plane names.

Typography rhythm
	•	Headline size: clamp(28px, 4.2vw, 48px)
	•	Subhead size: clamp(17px, 2.2vw, 24px)
	•	Body text: 15 to 16px with 1.45 line height
	•	Use tracked caps sparingly for small section titles.

Do not change
	•	Do not tint or texture the 3D canvas with warm panel colors or paper effects.
	•	The user must feel they are moving in real space while the surrounding UI uses the serif-forward retro print aesthetic.